   {:e #blake3 "cb5548b2d6697d0c772728f5b023c5088cbf66eb1034fbf7a08d349538a01e35" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :recon/trace-71207fed216922b6; Session entity: :recon/trace-31f48f0a5edf56eb; Session entity: :recon/trace-d424ae65a830a9c4; TASK TITLE/BODY SPLIT — THE DATA MODEL FIX. Root cause of recurring duplicate detection failures: CRB reconciliation searches 500-char title text where signal (activation pattern) is 15 chars diluted in 485 chars of BACKGROUND noise. We built graph traversal, IDF weighting, L-infinity norms — and OAO still duplicated ZCM. The pattern: we keep optimizing the SCORING FUNCTION when the problem is the INPUT REPRESENTATION. The fix: split :task/title into :task/title (<=120 chars, activation pattern ONLY) and :task/body (everything after BACKGROUND:). Every downstream system immediately improves without changes: CRB searches concentrated signal, TSV title column is naturally short, R(t) labels are compact, seed demonstrations match on clean titles, spec_graph_neighbors parses fewer false-positive refs. The short_title function becomes unnecessary — it was a bandaid for a data model problem. This is the minimum structural change from the Task-as-ACP EPIC (t-ca43c759) that delivers maximum downstream benefit. APPROACH: (1) Add :task/body (String, One) schema attribute. (2) In task create, split at first BACKGROUND: marker — title gets everything before, body gets everything after. (3) In task show, display both (title as header, body as expandable context). (4) In task list, title field is already short — no truncation needed. (5) Existing tasks with embedded BACKGROUND: in title continue to work via short_title fallback. New tasks store clean. TRACES TO: INV-INTERFACE-008, INV-GUIDANCE-024, INV-TASK-005.; Session entity: :recon/trace-663354677649d81a\nSession entity: :task/t-99d31560; Session entity: :task/t-80e46872" :op :assert}
